<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67cd0b0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7316"><num value="7316">§ 7316.</num><heading> Lifeboatmen</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To qualify for an endorsement as lifeboatman, an applicant must provide satisfactory proof that the applicant—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf67cd0b1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7316/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> has the service or training required by regulation;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf67cd0b2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7316/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> is qualified professionally as demonstrated by examination; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf67cd0b3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7316/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> is qualified professionally by actual demonstration.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf67cd0b4-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/544">97 Stat. 544</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
